claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table titled “TABLE 1. Influenza vaccines — United States, 2023–24 influenza season” listing multiple influenza vaccines (egg-based standard-dose IIV4, cell culture–based ccIIV4, high-dose IIV4, etc.) with columns for trade name/manufacturer, presentation, age indication, hemagglutinin (HA) micrograms per dose or virus count, route of administration, and mercury content. The table does not present any information about antigenic match between Flublok and WHO- or FDA-selected strains, so it does not support the claim. Note: Image quality is sufficient to see headings and data; however, no strain-match details are included in the visible portion of the table.
